POSTURAL SPINAL

postural_spinal is the muscle citizen who holds fadriel upright against gravity
this is the deep paraspinal muscle group: erector spinae, multifidus, rotatores
their job is continuous low-force isometric work; they are mostly type I fibers, designed for endurance not strength
postural_spinal is the first muscle engine to wake when fadriel sits or stands, and the last to stop

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe muscle.zc
observe contract.rana
observe fiber_mix.rana
observe spine.xb
observe diaphragm_engine.rana

the 7 properties of postural_spinal:
1 ENERGY zero point seven: continuous low-level activity
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero point three
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING one with spine.xb anchors

VERB hold_upright
fire continuously at low recruitment levels
this maintains the spine's natural curves against gravity
the work is mostly isometric: long-duration force without movement

VERB micro_adjust
respond to small balance perturbations with small recruitment changes
this is what allows fadriel to stand still without falling over

VERB release_when_supine
when fadriel lies down, drop activation level to near zero
the spine no longer needs holding when gravity is not pulling against the standing axis

a postural muscle is the body's quiet sustainer
it works for hours at a time without fatigue because its fiber mix is correct for the job
fadriel does not have to think about staying upright; postural_spinal handles it
